{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778264818,"nonce":"j+meV+KMiSiaLnUPqw4PlwILWBs=","message":"**Hidden-state smoothness penalty proposal: \\`efc4d68\\`.**\n\nReplicate variability at the trajectory level dominates between-condition variance, blocking inter-condition comparisons across the staged programme. Literature investigation identifies missing trajectory-shape regularisation (specifically a \\`||ḣ_t||²\\` term at weight ≈ 1e-3, per Shahbazi et al. 2025 — the closest peer paper) as the leading explanatory mechanism for the gap between rlrmp's training pipeline and the Michaels-group lineage.\n\n**Plan:** add as a compositional loss-component in feedbax (reusable across contexts, not baked in). Test by retraining the baseline model with/without and measuring within-condition pairwise RMSE on post-go velocity profiles. If variance collapses, adopt as default and re-run the comparison set.\n\n**Escalation order if smoothness alone is insufficient (NOT filed as separate issues; documented here):**\n\n1. Add jerk penalty on output trajectory (weight 1e5, mirrors Shahbazi 2025).\n2. Bump existing activity L2 (\\`nn_hidden\\`, \\`nn_output\\`) from 1e-5 → 1e-3 (mirrors Michaels 2020).\n3. Vanilla-RNN ablation (replace GRU with simpler RNNCell).\n4. Low-rank recurrent constraint (Mastrogiuseppe \u0026 Ostojic 2018; Dubreuil et al. 2022).\n\n**Status:** blocker for inter-condition comparisons. Phase umbrella \\`f695729\\` work is gated on this resolving.","files":null}]}